Nchf_OfflineOnlyCharging (1.0.2)

Download OpenAPI specification:

OfflineOnlyCharging Service © 2022, 3GPP Organizational Partners (ARIB, ATIS, CCSA, ETSI, TSDSI, TTA, TTC). All rights reserved.

3GPP TS 32.291 V17.0.0: Telecommunication management; Charging management; 5G system, charging service; Stage 3.

/offlinechargingdata

Authorizations:
NoneoAuth2ClientCredentials
Request Body schema: application/json
required
subscriberIdentifier
string (Supi) ^(imsi-[0-9]{5,15}|nai-.+|gci-.+|gli-.+|.+)$

String identifying a Supi that shall contain either an IMSI, a network specific identifier, a Global Cable Identifier (GCI) or a Global Line Identifier (GLI) as specified in clause 2.2A of 3GPP TS 23.003. It shall be formatted as follows

  • for an IMSI "imsi-", where shall be formatted according to clause 2.2 of 3GPP TS 23.003 that describes an IMSI.
  • for a network specific identifier "nai-, where shall be formatted according to clause 28.7.2 of 3GPP TS 23.003 that describes an NAI.
  • for a GCI "gci-", where shall be formatted according to clause 28.15.2 of 3GPP TS 23.003.
  • for a GLI "gli-", where shall be formatted according to clause 28.16.2 of 3GPP TS 23.003.To enable that the value is used as part of an URI, the string shall only contain characters allowed according to the "lower-with-hyphen" naming convention defined in 3GPP TS 29.501.
required
object (NFIdentification)
invocationTimeStamp
required
string <date-time> (DateTime)

string with format 'date-time' as defined in OpenAPI.

invocationSequenceNumber
required
integer (Uint32) [ 0 .. 4294967295 ]

Integer where the allowed values correspond to the value range of an unsigned 32-bit integer.

retransmissionIndicator
boolean
serviceSpecificationInfo
string
Array of objects (MultipleUnitUsage) >= 0 items
Array of objects (Trigger) >= 0 items
object (PDUSessionChargingInformation)
object (RoamingQBCInformation)

Responses

/{apiRoot}/nchf-offlineonlycharging/v1/offlinechargingdata

/offlinechargingdata/{OfflineChargingDataRef}/update

Authorizations:
NoneoAuth2ClientCredentials
path Parameters
OfflineChargingDataRef
required
string

a unique identifier for a charging data resource in a PLMN

Request Body schema: application/json
required
subscriberIdentifier
string (Supi) ^(imsi-[0-9]{5,15}|nai-.+|gci-.+|gli-.+|.+)$

String identifying a Supi that shall contain either an IMSI, a network specific identifier, a Global Cable Identifier (GCI) or a Global Line Identifier (GLI) as specified in clause 2.2A of 3GPP TS 23.003. It shall be formatted as follows

  • for an IMSI "imsi-", where shall be formatted according to clause 2.2 of 3GPP TS 23.003 that describes an IMSI.
  • for a network specific identifier "nai-, where shall be formatted according to clause 28.7.2 of 3GPP TS 23.003 that describes an NAI.
  • for a GCI "gci-", where shall be formatted according to clause 28.15.2 of 3GPP TS 23.003.
  • for a GLI "gli-", where shall be formatted according to clause 28.16.2 of 3GPP TS 23.003.To enable that the value is used as part of an URI, the string shall only contain characters allowed according to the "lower-with-hyphen" naming convention defined in 3GPP TS 29.501.
required
object (NFIdentification)
invocationTimeStamp
required
string <date-time> (DateTime)

string with format 'date-time' as defined in OpenAPI.

invocationSequenceNumber
required
integer (Uint32) [ 0 .. 4294967295 ]

Integer where the allowed values correspond to the value range of an unsigned 32-bit integer.

retransmissionIndicator
boolean
serviceSpecificationInfo
string
Array of objects (MultipleUnitUsage) >= 0 items
Array of objects (Trigger) >= 0 items
object (PDUSessionChargingInformation)
object (RoamingQBCInformation)

Responses

/{apiRoot}/nchf-offlineonlycharging/v1/offlinechargingdata/{OfflineChargingDataRef}/update

/offlinechargingdata/{OfflineChargingDataRef}/release

Authorizations:
NoneoAuth2ClientCredentials
path Parameters
OfflineChargingDataRef
required
string

a unique identifier for a charging data resource in a PLMN

Request Body schema: application/json
required
subscriberIdentifier
string (Supi) ^(imsi-[0-9]{5,15}|nai-.+|gci-.+|gli-.+|.+)$

String identifying a Supi that shall contain either an IMSI, a network specific identifier, a Global Cable Identifier (GCI) or a Global Line Identifier (GLI) as specified in clause 2.2A of 3GPP TS 23.003. It shall be formatted as follows

  • for an IMSI "imsi-", where shall be formatted according to clause 2.2 of 3GPP TS 23.003 that describes an IMSI.
  • for a network specific identifier "nai-, where shall be formatted according to clause 28.7.2 of 3GPP TS 23.003 that describes an NAI.
  • for a GCI "gci-", where shall be formatted according to clause 28.15.2 of 3GPP TS 23.003.
  • for a GLI "gli-", where shall be formatted according to clause 28.16.2 of 3GPP TS 23.003.To enable that the value is used as part of an URI, the string shall only contain characters allowed according to the "lower-with-hyphen" naming convention defined in 3GPP TS 29.501.
required
object (NFIdentification)
invocationTimeStamp
required
string <date-time> (DateTime)

string with format 'date-time' as defined in OpenAPI.

invocationSequenceNumber
required
integer (Uint32) [ 0 .. 4294967295 ]

Integer where the allowed values correspond to the value range of an unsigned 32-bit integer.

retransmissionIndicator
boolean
serviceSpecificationInfo
string
Array of objects (MultipleUnitUsage) >= 0 items
Array of objects (Trigger) >= 0 items
object (PDUSessionChargingInformation)
object (RoamingQBCInformation)

/{apiRoot}/nchf-offlineonlycharging/v1/offlinechargingdata/{OfflineChargingDataRef}/release
